1 pursuant to G.S. 7A-308(a)(11) are payable to the clerk of the superior court at the time the
2 certificate is filed.
3 (i) Immediately upon the docketing and indexing of a certificate as provided in
4 subsection (h) of this section, the assessments, including taxes, penalties, interest, and costs,
5 constitute a valid judgment against the timeshare described in the judgment with the priority
6 provided for claims of lien in G.S. 93A-62(d)(2). The judgment, except as expressly provided in
7 this section, has the same force and effect as a duly rendered judgment of the superior court
8 directing sale of the timeshare for the satisfaction of the assessment lien, and it shall bear interest
9 at an annual rate of eight percent (8%).
10 (j) At any time prior to the issuance of a certificate of sale in accordance with subdivision
11 (8) of subsection (l) of this section, any person entitled to notice under this section may appear
12 before the clerk of superior court and move to set aside the judgment on the ground that the
13 assessment has been paid or that the assessment lien on which the judgment is based is invalid.
14 (k) Upon payment in full of any judgment docketed under this section, together with
15 interest and costs accrued to the date of payment, the managing entity, holder of the lien, or
16 designated trustee receiving payment shall certify the fact of the payment to the clerk of superior
17 court and cancel the judgment.
18 (l) At any time after 30 days and before one year from the indexing of the judgment as
19 provided in subsection (h) of this section, at the request of the managing entity or holder of the
20 lien, the timeshare shall be sold by a trustee in a public auction held in the county in which the
21 timeshare project is located on the date, location, and starting time designated in the notice of
22 sale sent in accordance with this subsection. The trustee's sale shall occur at a location consistent
23 with G.S. 45-21.4. The timeshare trustee foreclosure sale shall be conducted in accordance with
24 the following:
25 (1) The managing entity or the holder of the lien shall appoint a trustee, who shall
26 conduct the sale and act as the auctioneer. The appointment of the trustee shall
27 be included in the claim of lien or the certificate. The managing entity or the
28 holder of the lien, at its option, may from time to time remove a trustee
29 previously appointed and appoint a successor trustee by filing a substitution
30 of trustee with the clerk of superior court. Counsel for the managing entity or
31 for the holder of the lien may be appointed by the managing entity or by the
32 holder of the lien to serve as the trustee and may serve in that capacity as long
33 as the owner does not contest the obligation to pay the amount of any sums
34 due the managing entity or the holder of the lien, or the validity, enforcement,
35 or foreclosure of the claim of lien as provided in subsection (e) of this section.
36 A trustee appointed pursuant to this subsection shall have the same fiduciary
37 duties and obligations as a trustee in the foreclosure of a deed of trust and is a
38 neutral third party. While serving as trustee in the foreclosure proceeding, a
39 trustee may not advocate for the managing entity or the holder of the lien or
40 the owner of the timeshare subject to foreclosure. The trustee shall be entitled
41 to a commission for services rendered which shall include fees, costs, and
42 expenses reasonably incurred by the trustee in connection with the timeshare
43 trustee foreclosure procedure, whether or not a sale is held. The trustee's
44 commission shall be paid without regard to any limitations on compensation
45 otherwise provided by law, including, without limitation, the provisions of
46 G.S. 45-21.15. The trustee may use a third party to conduct the sale on behalf
47 of the trustee and the trustee is liable for the conduct of the sale and the actions
48 of the third party with respect to the conduct of the sale.
49 (2) At least 30 days prior to the day fixed for the timeshare trustee foreclosure,
50 the trustee shall send notice by registered or certified mail, return receipt
51 requested, or by designated delivery service pursuant to 26 U.S.C. §
