36 set forth in the notice of sale, as described in subdivision (3) of this subsection.
37 (8) On the date of sale and upon receipt of the cash or certified funds due from
38 the highest bidder, the trustee shall issue to the highest bidder a certificate of
39 sale stating that a foreclosure conforming to the requirements of this section
40 has occurred. The certificate shall include the time, location, and date of the
41 sale, that the timeshare was sold, the amounts secured by the lien, and the
42 amount of the highest bid. A copy of the certificate shall be mailed by
43 first-class mail to the owner's address as recorded in the books and records of
44 the timeshare program. Upon issuance of a certificate of sale, all rights of
45 redemption are foreclosed and shall terminate.
46 (m) A sale conducted under this section releases the owner from liability for all amounts
47 secured by the lien. The managing entity or holder of the lien have no right to a deficiency
48 judgment against the owner after a sale of the owner's timeshare under this section.
49 (n) Within 10 calendar days after the trustee conducts a sale under this section, the trustee
50 shall execute and file with the clerk of superior court, a certificate of compliance that has been
51 signed and sworn to or affirmed before a notary public. In furtherance of the execution of the
