17 SECTION 3. G.S. 29-19 reads as rewritten:
18 "§ 29-19. Succession by, through and from children born out of wedlock.
19 …
20 (b) For purposes of intestate succession, a child born out of wedlock shall be entitled to
21 take by, through and from:
22 (1) Any person who has been finally adjudged to be the father of the child
23 pursuant to the provisions of G.S. 49-1 through 49-9 or the provisions of
24 G.S. 49-14 through 49-16;49-16.
25 (2) Any person who has acknowledged himself during his own lifetime and the
26 child's lifetime to be the father of the child in a written instrument executed or
27 acknowledged before a certifying officer named in G.S. 52-10(b) and filed
28 during his own lifetime and the child's lifetime in the office of the clerk of
29 superior court of the county where either he or the child resides.G.S. 52-10(b).
30 …."
31 SECTION 4. G.S. 130A-101(f) reads as rewritten:
32 "(f) If the mother was unmarried at all times from date of conception through date of birth,
33 the name of the father shall not be entered on the certificate unless the child's mother and father
34 complete an affidavit acknowledging paternity which contains the following:
35 (1) A sworn statement by the mother consenting to the assertion of paternity by
36 the father and declaring that the father is the child's natural father and that the
37 mother was unmarried at all times from the date of conception through the
38 date of birth;
39 (2) A sworn statement by the father declaring that he believes he is the natural
40 father of the child;
41 (3) Information explaining in plain language the effect of signing the affidavit,
42 including a statement of parental rights and responsibilities and an
43 acknowledgment of the receipt of this information; and
44 (4) The social security numbers of both parents.
45 The State Registrar, in consultation with the Child Support Enforcement Section of the
46 Division of Social Services, shall develop and disseminate a form affidavit for use in compliance
47 with this section, together with an information sheet that contains all the information required to
48 be disclosed by subdivision (3) of this subsection.
49 Upon the execution of the affidavit, the declaring father shall be listed as the father on the
50 birth certificate, subject to the declaring father's right to rescind under G.S. 110-132. The
51 executed affidavit shall be filed with the registrar along with the birth certificate. In the event
House Bill 992-Fifth Edition Page 9

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 paternity is properly placed at issue, a certified copy of the affidavit shall be admissible in any
2 action to establish paternity. The surname of the child shall be determined by the mother, except
3 if the father's name is entered on the certificate, the mother and father shall agree upon the child's
4 surname. If there is no agreement, the child's surname shall be the same as that of the mother.
5 The execution and filing of this affidavit with the registrar does not affect rights of inheritance
6 unless the affidavit is also filed with the clerk of court in accordance with G.S. 29-19(b)(2)."
7 SECTION 5. Sections 1 and 2 of this act become effective December 1, 2025, and
8 apply to claims of lien filed on or after that date. Sections 3 and 4 of this act become effective
9 December 1, 2025, and apply to the estates of decedents dying on or after that date. The remainder
10 of this act is effective when it becomes law.
